{"title_page": "72nd Venice International Film Festival", "text_new": "{{short description|Film festival}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox Film festival\n|name = <small>72nd Venice International Film Festival</small>\n|image = VeniceFilmFestival72poster.jpg\n|caption = Festival poster\n|opening = ''[[Everest (2015 film)|Everest]]''\n|closing = ''[[Mr. Six (film)|Mr. Six]]''\n|location = [[Venice]], Italy\n|founded = 1932\n|awards = [[Golden Lion]]: ''[[From Afar (film)|From Afar]]''<br>[[Silver Lion]]: [[Pablo Trapero]]\n|host = [[Elisa Sednaoui]]\n|number = \n|date = 2 \u2013 12 September 2015\n|website = [http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/ Website]\n| chronology     = Venice Film Festival\n| preceded_by    = [[71st Venice International Film Festival|71st]]\n| followed_by    = [[73rd Venice International Film Festival|73rd]]\n}}\n[[File:Logo Venezia 2015.jpg|thumb|right|300px|72nd Venice International Film Festival]]\nThe '''72nd annual [[Venice Film Festival|Venice International Film Festival]]''' took place from 2 to 12 September 2015.<ref name=\"Venice2015\">{{cite web |url=http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/72nd-festival/line-up |title=72nd Venice International Film Festival, Line-up |work=labiennale.org |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150926101732/http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/72nd-festival/line-up |archivedate=26 September 2015 }}</ref> [[Alfonso Cuar\u00f3n]] served as the President of the Jury for the main competition.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/news/11-05.html |title=Director Alfonso Cuar\u00f3n President of the International Jury for the Venezia 72 Competition |date=11 May 2015 |accessdate=11 May 2015 |work=Venice Biennale}}</ref> A restored version of [[Federico Fellini]]'s film ''[[Amarcord]]'' was shown at the festival.<ref name=\"Amarcord\">{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2015/film/global/venice-fest-to-bow-freshly-restored-copy-of-federico-fellinis-amarcord-1201519661/ |title=Venice Fest To Bow Freshly Restored Copy Of Federico Fellini\u2019s \u2018Amarcord\u2019 |accessdate=15 June 2015 |work=Variety}}</ref> The Venezuelan film ''[[From Afar (film)|From Afar]]'' by [[Lorenzo Vigas]] won the [[Golden Lion]] award.<ref name=\"winners\" />\n\n''[[Everest (2015 film)|Everest]]'' was selected as the festival's opening night film,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2015/07/baltasar-kormakurs-everest-venice-film-festival-universal-working-title-1201472041/ |title=Baltasar Korm\u00e1kur\u2019s \u2018Everest\u2019 To Open Venice Film Festival |author=Ali Jaafar |date=8 July 2015 |accessdate=8 July 2015 |work=Deadline Hollywood}}</ref> while [[Guan Hu]]'s drama film ''[[Mr. Six (film)|Mr. Six]]'' served as the closing night film.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/venice-film-festival-unveils-lineup-811809|title=Venice Film Festival Unveils Star-Studded Lineup for 72nd Edition|accessdate=29 July 2015}}</ref> Actress and director [[Elisa Sednaoui]] hosted the opening and closing ceremonies of the festival.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/news/27-04.html|title=Elisa Sednaoui to host the opening and closing nights of Venezia 72|accessdate=29 July 2015|work=Venice Biennale|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150905025824/http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/news/27-04.html|archive-date=5 September 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nThe festival poster featured [[Nastassja Kinski]] in front as reminiscent of [[Wim Wenders]]'s [[Paris, Texas (film)|Paris, Texas]], while in background it featured the character of [[Antoine Doinel]] portrayed by [[Jean-Pierre L\u00e9aud]] from [[Fran\u00e7ois Truffaut]]'s 1959 [[drama film]] ''[[The 400 Blows]]'', which also appeared in [[71st Venice International Film Festival]] poster.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/venice-2015-film-festival-poster-806810|title=Venice: 2015 Film Festival Poster Unveiled|accessdate=29 July 2015 |work=The Hollywood Reporter}}</ref>\n\nThe festival honoured [[Brian De Palma]] with ''Glory to the Filmmaker Award'' and a documentary film titled ''[[De Palma (film)|De Palma]]'' by [[Noah Baumbach]] and [[Jake Paltrow]] also screened at the festival.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ew.com/article/2015/08/13/brian-de-palma-venice-film-festival|title=Brian De Palma to receive award at the Venice Film Festival|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=13 August 2015|accessdate=29 August 2015}}</ref> [[Jonathan Demme]] received the ''Persol Tribute to Visionary Talent Award'', who also served as the President of ''Horizons (Orizzonti)'' section jury.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2015/film/festivals/jonathan-demme-to-receive-visionary-talent-award-in-venice-1201580580/|title=Jonathan Demme to Receive Visionary Talent Award in Venice|work=Variety|date=28 August 2015|accessdate=29 August 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Juries==\nThe following people formed the 2015 juries:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/72nd-festival/juries/ |title=International Juries of the 72nd Venice Film Festival |work=labiennale.org |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150926111117/http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/72nd-festival/juries/ |archivedate=26 September 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ew.com/article/2015/07/27/venice-film-festival-jury-elizabeth-banks|title=Elizabeth Banks, Diane Kruger join Alfonso Cuar\u00f3n on Venice Film Festival jury|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=27 July 2015|accessdate=29 July 2015}}</ref>\n\n'''Main competition (Venezia 72)'''\n*[[Alfonso Cuar\u00f3n]], Mexican director (Jury President)\n*[[Elizabeth Banks]], American actress and director\n*[[Diane Kruger]], German actress\n*[[Emmanuel Carr\u00e8re]], French author, screenwriter and director \n*[[Nuri Bilge Ceylan]], Turkish director\n*[[Pawel Pawlikowski]], Polish director\n*[[Francesco Munzi]], Italian director\n*[[Hou Hsiao-hsien]], Taiwanese director\n*[[Lynne Ramsay]], Scottish director and screenwriter\n\n'''Horizons (Orizzonti)'''\n*[[Jonathan Demme]], American director  (President) \n*[[Alix Delaporte]], French director and screenwriter \n*[[Paz Vega]], Spanish actress \n*[[Fruit Chan]], Hong Kong director\n*[[Anita Caprioli]], Italian actress\n\n'''Opera Prima''' (Venice Award for a Debut Film)\n*[[Saverio Costanzo]], Italian director  (President)\n*[[Roger Garcia]], Hong Kong producer\n* Natacha Laurent, French film critic and historian \n*[[Charles Burnett (director)|Charles Burnett]], American director\n* Daniela Michel, Mexican journalist\n\n==Official selection==\n===In Competition===\nThe following films were selected for the main competition:<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/72nd-festival/line-up/off-sel/venezia72/ |title=Venezia 72 |work=labiennale.org |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151001042022/http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/72nd-festival/line-up/off-sel/venezia72/ |archivedate=1 October 2015  |access-date=14 April 2018 }}</ref><ref name=\"InComp\">{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2015/07/venice-film-festival-lineup-2015-full-list-1201486791/|title=Venice Film Festival: Lido Lineup Builds Awards Season Buzz \u2013 Full List |accessdate=29 July 2015 |work=Deadline}}</ref><ref name=\"Variety\">{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2015/film/news/venice-fest-reveals-robust-lineup-featuring-hollywood-stars-and-international-auteurs-1201551960/|title=Venice Fest Reveals Robust Lineup Featuring Hollywood Stars and International Auteurs |accessdate=29 July 2015 |work=Variety}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\" style=\"width:95%; margin-bottom:0px\"\n|-\n! English title\n! Original title\n! Director(s)\n! Production country\n|-\n| ''[[11 Minutes (film)|11 Minutes]]'' || ''11 minut'' || data-sort-value=\"Skolimowsk\"| [[Jerzy Skolimowski]] || Poland\n|-\n| colspan=2| ''[[Anomalisa (film)|Anomalisa]]'' || data-sort-value=\"Kaufman\"| [[Charlie Kaufman]