 del lago salato'' || [[Andrea Segre]] || Italy\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:95%; margin-top:2px\"\n! colspan=4| Lux Prize\n|-\n! English title\n! Original title\n! Director(s)\n! Production country\n|-\n| colspan=2| ''[[Mediterranea (film)|Mediterranea]]'' || [[Jonas Carpignano]] || Italy, United States, Germany, France, Qatar\n|-\n| colspan=2| ''[[Mustang (film)|Mustang]]'' || [[Deniz Gamze Erg\u00fcven]] || France, Germany, Turkey, Qatar\n|-\n| ''[[The Lesson (2014 Bulgarian film)|The Lesson]]'' || ''Urok'' || Kristina Grozeva, Petar Valchanov || Bulgaria, Greece\n|}\n:<span style=\"background:#FFDEAD\">Highlighted title</span> indicates the official Venice Days Award winner.\n\n== Awards ==\n[[File:Golden Lion for Best Film frim afar (25530461470).jpg|thumb|[[Lorenzo Vigas]] with the [[Golden Lion]] for ''[[From Afar (film)|From Afar]]'']]\n[[File:Valeria Golino, Venice 2015 (cropped).jpg|thumb|[[Valeria Golino]], winner of the [[Coppa Volpi]]]]\n[[File:Abraham Attah (cropped).jpg|thumb|[[Abraham Attah]], winner of the [[Marcello Mastroianni Award]]]]\n\n===Official selection===\nThe following Official Awards were presented at the 72nd edition:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/72nd-festival/awards/ |title=Official Awards of the 72nd Venice Film Festival |work=labiennale.org |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150926125200/http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/72nd-festival/awards/ |archivedate=26 September 2015 }}</ref><ref name=\"winners\">{{cite web|title=LIVE: The winners of the 72nd Venice Film Festival|url=http://cineuropa.org/nw.aspx?t=newsdetail&did=298479|accessdate=12 September 2015}}</ref>\n\n'''In Competition (Venezia 72)'''\n*[[Golden Lion]]: ''[[From Afar (film)|From Afar]]'' by [[Lorenzo Vigas]]\n*[[Silver Lion|Silver Lion for Best Director]]: [[Pablo Trapero]] for ''[[The Clan (2015 film)|The Clan]]''\n*[[Grand Jury Prize (Venice Film Festival)|Grand Jury Prize]]: ''[[Anomalisa]]'' by [[Charlie Kaufman]] and [[Duke Johnson (director)|Duke Johnson]]\n*[[Volpi Cup for Best Actor]]: [[Fabrice Luchini]] for ''[[Courted (film)|Courted]]''\n*[[Volpi Cup for Best Actress]]: [[Valeria Golino]] for ''[[Per amor vostro]]''\n*[[Marcello Mastroianni Award]]: [[Abraham Attah]] for ''[[Beasts of No Nation (film)|Beasts of No Nation]]''\n*Best Screenplay Award: [[Christian Vincent (director)|Christian Vincent]] for ''[[Courted (film)|Courted]]''\n*[[Special Jury Prize (Venice Film Festival)|Special Jury Prize]]: ''[[Frenzy (2015 film)|Frenzy]]'' by [[Emin Alper]]\n\n'''Horizons (Orizzonti)'''\n*Best Film: ''[[Free in Deed]]'' by [[Jake Mahaffy]]\n*Best Director: [[Brady Corbet]] for ''[[The Childhood of a Leader (film)|The Childhood of a Leader]]''\n*Special Jury Prize: ''[[Neon Bull]]'' by [[Gabriel Mascaro]]\n*Special Prize For Best Actor or Actress: Dominique Leborne for ''[[Temp\u00eate (film)|Temp\u00eate]]''\n*Horizons Prize for Best Short: ''[[Belladonna (short film)|Belladonna]]'' by Dubravka Turic\n\n'''Lion of the Future''' \n:Luigi De Laurentiis Award for a Debut Film: ''The Childhood of a Leader'' by Brady Corbet (Horizons)<ref>{{cite web|title=Venice: Robert Pattinson-Starrer 'Childhood of a Leader' Wins Best Debut Film|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/venice-robert-pattinson-starrer-childhood-822550|accessdate=12 September 2015}}</ref>\n\n'''Venice Classics Awards'''\n*Best Documentary on Cinema: ''The 1000 Eyes of Dr. Maddin'' by Yves Montmayeur\n*Best Restored Film: ''[[Sal\u00f2, or the 120 Days of Sodom]]'' by [[Pier Paolo Pasolini]]\n\n'''Special Awards'''\n*[[Golden Lion#Golden Lion Honorary Award|Golden Lion For Lifetime Achievement]]: [[Bertrand Tavernier]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ilgazzettino.it/CULTURA/cinema_francese_tavernier_leone_d_amp_39_oro_carriera/notizie/1555371.shtml|title=Tavernier, Leone alla carriera: \"Fiero di ci\u00f2 che ho fatto\"|work=ilgazzettino.it}}</ref>\n*Jaeger-LeCoultre Glory to the Filmmaker Award: [[Brian De Palma]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dazebaonews.it/cultura/item/36049-venezia-72-il-premio-jaeger-lecoultre-glory-to-the-filmaker-a-brian-de-palma.html|title=Venezia 72. Il premio Jaeger-LeCoultre Glory to the Filmaker a Brian De Palma|author=Redazione|work=dazebaonews.it}}</ref>\n*Persol Tribute To Visionary Talent Award: [[Jonathan Demme]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.luukmagazine.com/jonathan-demme-vince-il-persol-tribute-to-visionary-talent-award-2015/|title=Jonathan Demme vince il Persol Tribute to Visionary Talent Award 2015|work=luukmagazine.com|date=8 September 2015|accessdate=9 September 2015}}</ref>\n*L'Or\u00e9al Paris per il Cinema Award: Valentina Corti\n\n===Autonomous sections===\nThe following official and collateral awards were conferred to films of the autonomous sections:<ref name=\"collateral\">{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/event/ev0000681/2015/1/ |title=Venice Film Festival 2015 Awards |work=imdb.com |accessdate=7 May 2018}}</ref>\n\n'''30th Venice International Critics' Week'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sicvenezia.it/3559/edizione-2015/news-2015/premio-del-pubblico-pietro-barzisa-a-tanna/?lang=en |title=All Awards 2015 announced: Audience Award Pietro Barzisa to Tanna by Bentley Dean and Martin Butler}}</ref> \n*Audience Award Pietro Barzisa: ''[[Tanna (film)|Tanna]]'' by [[Bentley Dean]] and [[Martin Butler (director)|Martin Butler]]\n* Fedeora Awards (Critics' Week):\n**Best Film: ''[[The Black Hen]]'' by [[Min Bahadur Bham]]\n**Best Cinematography: [[Bentley Dean]] for ''[[Tanna (film)|Tanna]]''\n\n'''Venice Days'''<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.venice-days.com/NEWS.asp?id=1&id_dettaglio=652&lang=eng |title=Palmares 2015 |work=Venice Days}}</ref>\n*Venice Days Award: ''[[Early Winter (film)|Early Winter]]'' by [[Michael Rowe (director)|Michael Rowe]]\n*BNL People's Choice Award: ''[[As I Open My Eyes]]'' by  [[Leyla Bouzid]]\n*Europa Cinemas Label Award for Best European Film: ''[[As I Open My Eyes]]'' by  [[Leyla Bouzid]] \n*Laguna Sud Award:\n**Best Film: ''[[Lolo (film)|Lolo]]'' directed by [[Julie Delpy]]\n**Best Italian Discovery: ''[[Arianna (film 2015)|Arianna]]'' directed by [[Carlo Lavagna]]\n* Francesco Pasinetti (SNGCI) Award - Special mentions:\n**''[[First Light (film)|First Light]]'' (''La prima luce'') by [[Vincenzo Marra]]\n**[[Vincenzo Marra]] (director) and [[Riccardo Scamarcio]] (leading actor) for 'First Light'''\n* Fedeora Awards (Venice Days):\n**Best Film: ''[[Underground Fragrance]]'' directed by [[Pengfei]] \n**Best Director of a Debut Film: Ruchika Oberoi for ''[[Island City (2015 film)|Island City]]''\n**Best Actress in a Debut Film: Ondina Quadri for ''Arianna''\n\n===Other collateral awards===\nThe following collateral awards were conferred to films of the official selection:<ref name=\"collateral\" />\n* [[FIPRESCI|FIPRESCI Awards]]<ref name=\"fipresci\">{{cite web|url=http://www.fipresci.org/festival-reports/2015/venice |title=FIPRESCI - Venice Awards 2015 |work=fipresci.org |accessdate=5 May 2018}}</ref>\n**Best Film (Main competition): ''[[Blood of My Blood (2015 film)|Blood of My Blood]]'' (''Sangue del mio sangue'') by [[Marco Bellocchio]]\n**Best Film (Horizons): ''[[Wednesday, 9 May]]'' (''Chaharshanbeh, 19 Ordibehesht'') by [[Vahid Jalilvand]]\n::Special mention: ''[[The Childhood of a Leader (film)|The Childhood of a Leader]]'' by [[Brady Corbet]]\n* [[SIGNIS|SIGNIS Award]]: ''[[Behemoth (2015 film)|Behemoth]]'' (''Bei xi mo shou'') by [[Zhao Liang (director)|Zhao Liang]]\n::Special mention: ''[[The Wait (2015 film)|The Wait]]'' (''L'attesa'') by [[Piero Messina]]\n* Francesco Pasinetti (SNGCI) Award:\n**Best Film: ''[[Don't Be Bad]]'' (''Non essere cattivo'') by  [[Claudio Caligari]]\n**Best Actor: [[Luca Marinelli]] for ''Don't Be Bad'' (Out of competition) \n**Best Actress: [[Valeria Golino]] for ''[[Per amor vostro|For Your Love]]''\n* Leoncino d'Oro Agiscuola Award: ''The Wait'' (''L'attesa'') by Piero Messina\n* Brian Award: ''[[Spotlight (film)|Spotlight]]'' by [[Tom McCarthy (director)|Tom McCarthy]]\n* [[Queer Lion]]: ''[[The Danish Girl (film)|The Danish Girl]]'' by [[Tom Hooper]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Eddie Redmayne\u2019s \u2018The Danish Girl\u2019 Wins Venice\u2019s Queer Lion Award as Oscar Buzz Mounts|url=https://www.thewrap.com/eddie-redmaynes-the-danish-girl-wins-venices-queer-lion-award-as-oscar-buzz-mounts/|accessdate=12 September 2015}}</ref>\n::Special mention: ''Baby Bump'' by Kuba Czekaj\n* Arca CinemaGiovani Award:\n**Best Film of Venezia 72: ''[[Frenzy (2015 film)|Frenzy]]'' by [[Emin Alper]]\n**Best Italian Film: ''[[Burning Love (film)|Burning Love]]'' (''Pecore in erba'') by Alberto Caviglia (Horizons)\n*FEDIC Award: ''Don't Be Bad'' directed by Claudio Caligari (Out of competition)\n::Special mention: ''[[The Wait (2015 film)|The Wait]]'' directed by [[Piero Messina]]\n* Fedeora Awards - Best Euro-Mediterranean film: ''[[Francofonia]]'' directed by [[Alexander Sokurov]]\n* Fondazione Mimmo Rotella Award: [[Alexander Sokurov]] for ''[[Francofonia]]''\n::Special Award: [[Johnny Depp]] and [[Terry Gilliam]]\n* 2nd Starlight Cinema Awards'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.comingsoon.it/news/?source=cinema&key=50196|title=Starlight Cinema Award 2015: i premiati a Venezia|work=ComingSoon.it}}</ref>\n**Career Award: [[Lina Wertmuller]]\n**International Award: [[Paz Vega]]\n**Best Film: [[Matteo Garrone|Matteo Garrone's]] ''[[Tale of Tales (2015 film)|Tale of Tales]]''\n**Best breakthrough actress of the year: Silvia D\u2019Amico\n***Best breakthrough actor of the year: Giovanni Anzaldo\n**Humanitarian Award: Myriam Catania\n**Special Mention: Lucana Film Commission\n**Best breakthrough production: ''Buena Onda'' by [[Riccardo Scamarcio]]\n**Intercultural Award: [[Reynaldo Gianecchini]]\n* Green Drop Award: ''[[Behemoth (2015 film)|Behemoth]]'' directed by [[Zhao Liang (director)|Zhao Liang]]\n* Vittorio Veneto Film Festival Young Jury award: ''[[Remember (2015 film)|Remember]]'' directed by [[Atom Egoyan]]\n::Special mention: ''[[11 Minutes (film)|11 Minutes]]'' directed by [[Jerzy Skolimowski]]\n* Gold Mouse: ''[[Rabin, the Last Day]]'' directed by [[Amos Gitai]]\n* Silver Mouse: ''[[Spotlight (film)|Spotlight]]'' directed by [[Tom McCarthy (director)|Tom McCarthy]]\n* Future Film Festival Digital Award: ''[[Anomalisa]]'' by [[Charlie Kaufman]] and [[Duke Johnson (director)|Duke Johnson]]\n::Special mention: ''[[Heart of a Dog]]'' by [[Laurie Anderson]]\n* P. Nazareno Taddei Award: ''[[Marguerite (2015 film)|Marguerite]]'' by [[Xavier Giannoli]]\n* Lanterna Magica (CGS) Award: ''Blanka'' by Kohki Hasei\n* Open Award: Carlotta Cerquetti for ''Harry\u2019s Bar''\n* Lina Mangiacapre Award: [[Laurie Anderson]] for ''[[Heart of a Dog (2015 film)|Heart of a Dog]]''\n* Gillo Pontecorvo - Arcobaleno Latino Award: ''[[Don't Be Bad]]'' by [[Claudio Caligari]]\n* INTERFILM Award: ''[[Wednesday, 9 May]]'' by [[Vahid Jalilvand]]\n* \"Civitas Vitae prossima\" Award: [[Alberto Caviglia]] for ''[[Pecore in erba]]''\n* Soundtrack Stars Award:\n**''[[A Bigger Splash (2015 film)|A Bigger Splash]]'' by [[Luca Guadagnino]]\n**''[[Equals (film)|Equals]]'' by [[Drake Doremus]]\n**Award for Lifetime Achievement: [[Nicola Piovani]]\n* Schermi di Qualit\u00e0 \u2013 Carlo Mazzacurati Award: ''[[Don't Be Bad]]'' by [[Claudio Caligari]]\n* Human Rights Nights Award: ''[[Rabin, the Last Day]]'' by [[Amos Gitai]]\n* AssoMusica \"Ho visto una Canzone\" Award: The song \"A cuor leggero\" by Riccardo Sinigallia, from the film ''[[Don't Be Bad]]'' \n* Sorriso diverso Venezia 2015 Award'''\n**Best Italian film: ''[[Don't Be Bad]]'' by [[Claudio Caligari]]\n**Best Film in a Foreign Language: ''Blanka'' by Kohki Hasei\n* Amnesty International Italia \"Il cinema per i diritti umani\" Award: ''[[Visaranai]]'' by [[Vetrimaaran]]\n* CITC \u2013 UNESCO 2015 Award: ''[[Beasts of No Nation (film)|Beasts of No Nation]]'' by [[Cary Fukunaga]]\n* NuovoImaie Talent Award:\n**Best Actress in a Debut Film: Ondina Quadri for ''Arianna'' \n**Best Italian actor in a Debut Film: [[Alessandro Borghi (actor)|Alessandro Borghi]] for ''[[Don't Be Bad]]''\n* Best Innovative Budget Award: ''[[A Bigger Splash (2015 film)|A Bigger Splash]]'' by [[Luca Guadagnino]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{official website|http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/}}\n*[https://www.imdb.com/event/ev0000681/2015/1/ Venice Film Festival 2015 Awards] on IMDb\n\n{{Venice Film Festival}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Venice Film Festival}}\n[[Category:Venice Film Festival|72]]\n[[Category:2015 film festivals]]\n[[Category:2015 festivals in Europe]]\n[[Category:2015 in Italian cinema]]\n[[Category:2010s in Venice|Film]]\n[[Category:September 2015 events in Italy]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Film festival}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}}\n{{Infobox Film festival\n|name = <small>72nd Venice International Film Festival</small>\n|image = VeniceFilmFestival72poster.jpg\n|caption = Festival poster\n|opening = ''[[Everest (2015 film)|Everest]]''\n|closing = ''[[Mr. Six (film)|Mr. Six]]''\n|location = [[Venice]], Italy\n|founded = 1932\n|awards = [[Golden Lion]]: ''[[From Afar (film)|From Afar]]''<br>[[Silver Lion]]: [[Pablo Trapero]]\n|host = [[Elisa Sednaoui]]\n|number = \n|date = 2 \u2013 12 September 2015\n|website = [http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/ Website]\n| chronology     = Venice Film Festival\n| preceded_by    = [[71st Venice International Film Festival|71st]]\n| followed_by    = [[73rd Venice International Film Festival|73rd]]\n}}\n[[File:Logo Venezia 2015.jpg|thumb|right|300px|72nd Venice International Film Festival]]\nThe '''72nd annual [[Venice Film Festival|Venice International Film Festival]]''' took place from 2 to 12 September 2015.<ref name=\"Venice2015\">{{cite web |url=http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/72nd-festival/line-up |title=72nd Venice International Film Festival, Line-up |work=labiennale.org |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150926101732/http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/72nd-festival/line-up |archivedate=26 September 2015 }}</ref> [[Alfonso Cuar\u00f3n]] served as the President of the Jury for the main competition.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/news/11-05.html |title=Director Alfonso Cuar\u00f3n President of the International Jury for the Venezia 72 Competition |date=11 May 2015 |accessdate=11 May 2015 |work=Venice Biennale}}</ref> A restored version of [[Federico Fellini]]'s film ''[[Amarcord]]'' was shown at the festival.<ref name=\"Amarcord\">{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2015/film/global/venice-fest-to-bow-freshly-restored-copy-of-federico-fellinis-amarcord-1201519661/ |title=Venice Fest To Bow Freshly Restored Copy Of Federico Fellini\u2019s \u2018Amarcord\u2019 |accessdate=15 June 2015 |work=Variety}}</ref> The Venezuelan film ''[[From Afar (film)|From Afar]]'' by [[Lorenzo Vigas]] won the [[Golden Lion]] award.<ref name=\"winners\" />\n\n''[[Everest (2015 film)|Everest]]'' was selected as the festival's opening night film,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2015/07/baltasar-kormakurs-everest-venice-film-festival-universal-working-title-1201472041/ |title=Baltasar Korm\u00e1kur\u2019s \u2018Everest\u2019 To Open Venice Film Festival |author=Ali Jaafar |date=8 July 2015 |accessdate=8 July 2015 |work=Deadline Hollywood}}</ref> while [[Guan Hu]]'s drama film ''[[Mr. Six (film)|Mr. Six]]'' served as the closing night film.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/venice-film-festival-unveils-lineup-811809|title=Venice Film Festival Unveils Star-Studded Lineup for 72nd Edition|accessdate=29 July 2015}}</ref> Actress and director [[Elisa Sednaoui]] hosted the opening and closing ceremonies of the festival.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/news/27-04.html|title=Elisa Sednaoui to host the opening and closing nights of Venezia 72|accessdate=29 July 2015|work=Venice Biennale|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150905025824/http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/news/27-04.html|archive-date=5 September 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nThe festival poster featured [[Nastassja Kinski]] in front as reminiscent of [[Wim Wenders]]'s [[Paris, Texas (film)|Paris, Texas]], while in background it featured the character of [[Antoine Doinel]] portrayed by [[Jean-Pierre L\u00e9aud]] from [[Fran\u00e7ois Truffaut]]'s 1959 [[drama film]] ''[[The 400 Blows]]'', which also appeared in [[71st Venice International Film Festival]] poster.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/venice-2015-film-festival-poster-806810|title=Venice: 2015 Film Festival Poster Unveiled|accessdate=29 July 2015 |work=The Hollywood Reporter}}</ref>\n\nThe festival honoured [[Brian De Palma]] with ''Glory to the Filmmaker Award'' and a documentary film titled ''[[De Palma (film)|De Palma]]'' by [[Noah Baumbach]] and [[Jake Paltrow]] also screened at the festival.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ew.com/article/2015/08/13/brian-de-palma-venice-film-festival|title=Brian De Palma to receive award at the Venice Film Festival|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=13 August 2015|accessdate=29 August 2015}}</ref> [[Jonathan Demme]] received the ''Persol Tribute to Visionary Talent Award'', who also served as the President of ''Horizons (Orizzonti)'' section jury.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2015/film/festivals/jonathan-demme-to-receive-visionary-talent-award-in-venice-1201580580/|title=Jonathan Demme to Receive Visionary Talent Award in Venice|work=Variety|date=28 August 2015|accessdate=29 August 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Juries==\nThe following people formed the 2015 juries:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/72nd-festival/juries/ |title=International Juries of the 72nd Venice Film Festival |work=labiennale.org |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150926111117/http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/72nd-festival/juries/ |archivedate=26 September 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ew.com/article/2015/07/27/venice-film-festival-jury-elizabeth-banks|title=Elizabeth Banks, Diane Kruger join Alfonso Cuar\u00f3n on Venice Film Festival jury|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=27 July 2015|accessdate=29 July 2015}}</ref>\n\n'''Main competition (Venezia 72)'''\n*[[Alfonso Cuar\u00f3n]], Mexican director (Jury President)\n*[[Elizabeth Banks]], American actress and director\n*[[Diane Kruger]], German actress\n*[[Emmanuel Carr\u00e8re]], French author, screenwriter and director \n*[[Nuri Bilge Ceylan]], Turkish director\n*[[Pawel Pawlikowski]], Polish director\n*[[Francesco Munzi]], Italian director\n*[[Hou Hsiao-hsien]], Taiwanese director\n*[[Lynne Ramsay]], Scottish director and screenwriter\n\n'''Horizons (Orizzonti)'''\n*[[Jonathan Demme]], American director  (President) \n*[[Alix Delaporte]], French director and screenwriter \n*[[Paz Vega]], Spanish actress \n*[[Fruit Chan]], Hong Kong director\n*[[Anita Caprioli]], Italian actress\n\n'''Opera Prima''' (Venice Award for a Debut Film)\n*[[Saverio Costanzo]], Italian director  (President)\n*[[Roger Garcia]], Hong Kong producer\n* Natacha Laurent, French film critic and historian \n*[[Charles Burnett (director)|Charles Burnett]], American director\n* Daniela Michel, Mexican journalist\n\n==Official selection==\n===In Competition===\nThe following films were selected for the main competition:<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/72nd-festival/line-up/off-sel/venezia72/ |title=Venezia 72 |work=labiennale.org |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151001042022/http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/72nd-festival/line-up/off-sel/venezia72/ |archivedate=1 October 2015  |access-date=14 April 2018 }}</ref><ref name=\"InComp\">{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2015/07/venice-film-festival-lineup-2015-full-list-1201486791/|title=Venice Film Festival: Lido Lineup Builds Awards Season Buzz \u2013 Full List |accessdate=29 July 2015 |work=Deadline}}</ref><ref name=\"Variety\">{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2015/film/news/venice-fest-reveals-robust-lineup-featuring-hollywood-stars-and-international-auteurs-1201551960/|title=Venice Fest Reveals Robust Lineup Featuring Hollywood Stars and International Auteurs |accessdate=29 July 2015 |work=Variety}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\" style=\"width:95%; margin-bottom:0px\"\n|-\n! English title\n! Original title\n! Director(s)\n! Production country\n|-\n| ''[[11 Minutes (film)|11 Minutes]]'' || ''11 minut'' || data-sort-value=\"Skolimowsk\"| [[Jerzy Skolimowski]] || Poland\n|-\n| colspan=2| ''[[Anomalisa (film)|Anomalisa]]'' || data-sort-value=\"Kaufman\"| [[Charlie Kaufman]], [[Duke Johnson (director)|Duke Johnson]] || United States \n|-\n| colspan=2| ''[[Beasts of No Nation (film)|Beasts of No Nation]]'' || data-sort-value=\"Fukunaga\"| [[Cary Fukunaga]] || United States\n|-\n| ''[[Behemoth (2015 film)|Behemoth]]'' || ''Bei xi mo shou'' ( \u60b2\u516e\u9b54\u517d ) || data-sort-value=\"Liang\"| [[Zhao Liang (director)|Zhao Liang]] || China, France\n|-\n| colspan=2 data-sort-value=\"Bigger\"| ''[[A Bigger Splash (2015 film)|A Bigger Splash]]'' || data-sort-value=\"Guadagnino\"| [[Luca Guadagnino]] || Italy, France\n|-\n| ''[[Blood of My Blood (2015 film)|Blood of My Blood]]'' || ''Sangue del mio sangue'' || data-sort-value=\"Bellocchio\"| [[Marco Bellocchio]] || Italy\n|-\n| data-sort-value=\"Clan\"| ''[[The Clan (2015 film)|The Clan]]'' || data-sort-value=\"Clan\"| ''El Clan'' || data-sort-value=\"Trapero\"| [[Pablo Trapero]] || Argentina, Spain\n|-\n| ''[[Courted (film)|Courted]]'' || data-sort-value=\"Hermine\"| ''L'Hermine'' || data-sort-value=\"Vincent\"| [[Christian Vincent (director)|Christian Vincent]] || France\n|-\n| colspan=2 data-sort-value=\"Danish\"| ''[[The Danish Girl (film)|The Danish Girl]]'' || data-sort-value=\"Hooper\"| [[Tom Hooper]] || United Kingdom, United States\n|-\n| colspan=2 data-sort-value=\"Endless\"| 