-sel/final-cut |archivedate=3 October 2015  |access-date=14 April 2018 }}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\" width=\"95%\"\n|-\n! English title\n! Original title\n! Director(s)\n! Production country\n|-\n| ''Ali, the Goat, and Ibrahim'' || ''Ali Mea'za We Ibrahim'' || data-sort-value=\"Elbendary\"| Sherif Elbendary || Egypt\n|-\n| ''House in the Fields'' || ''Tigmi Nigren'' || data-sort-value=\"Hadid\"| [[Tala Hadid]] || Morocco\n|-\n| ''Path of Paradise'' || ''Tarik Al-Jenah'' || data-sort-value=\"Al-Daradji\"| Atia Al-Daradji || Iraq\n|-\n| ''Rooster of Beirut'' || ''Deek Beirut'' || data-sort-value=\"Kalthoum\"| Ziad Kalthoum || Syria\n|-\n| ''Separation'' || ''Havibon'' || data-sort-value=\"Abdulqadir\"| Hakar Abdulqadir || Iraq\n|-\n| ''Zaineb Hates the Snow'' || ''Zaineb Takrahou Ethelj'' || data-sort-value=\"Ben Hania\"| [[Kaouther Ben Hania]] || Tunisia\n|}\n\n===Il Cinema nel Giardino===\nThe following feature films were selected for the ''Il Cinema nel Giardino'' section:<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.amica.it/2015/08/31/mostra-di-venezia-2015-il-calendario-eventi/ |title=Mostra di Venezia 2015: il calendario eventi |language=Italian |work=amica.it |accessdate=15 April 2018}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\" width=\"95%\"\n|-\n! Title\n! data-sort-type=\"number\"| Screening\n! Director(s)\n! Production country\n|-\n| ''Al centro del cinema'' || 6 Sep || data-sort-value=\"Caruso\"| Gianandrea Caruso, Chiara Dainese, Davide Minotti, Bernardo Pellegrini, Maria Tilli || Italy\n|-\n| ''Carlo Lizzani, Il mio cinema'' || 3 Sep || data-sort-value=\"Torelli\"| Roberto Torelli, Cristina Torelli, Paolo Luciani || Italy\n|-\n|  ''Il decalogo di Vasco'' || 11 Sep || data-sort-value=\"Masi\"| Fabio Masi || Italy\n|-\n| ''Torn'' (''Torn - Strappati'') || 9 Sep || data-sort-value=\"Gassmann\"| [[Alessandro Gassmann]] || Italy\n|-\n| ''Where is the Goldfish?'' (''Il pesce rosso dov'\u00e8?'') || 10 Sep || data-sort-value=\"Sgarbi\"| Elisabetta Sgarbi || Italy\n|-\n| ''[[Pino Zac#Documentary|ZAC - I Fiori del MALE]]'' || 8 Sep || data-sort-value=\"Denaro\"| Massimo Denaro || Italy\n|}\n\n==Autonomous sections==\n===International Critics\u2019 Week===\nThe following films were selected for the 29th Venice International Film Critics' Week:<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sicvenezia.it/edizione/30-settimana-internazionale-della-critica/?lang=en |title=30th International Film Critics\u2019 Week |work=sicvenezia.it |accessdate=14 April 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"Criticsweek\">{{cite web |url=http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/72nd-festival/line-up/aut-sect/sic/|title=International Critics\u2019 Week |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150925095415/http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/72nd-festival/line-up/aut-sect/sic/ |archivedate=25 September 2015 }}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\" style=\"width:95%; margin-bottom:0px\"\n! colspan=4| In competition\n|-\n! English title\n! Original title\n! Director(s)\n! Production country\n|-\n| ''[[Banat (The Journey)]]'' || ''Banat'' || data-sort-value=\"Valerio\"| Adriano Valerio || Italy, Romania, Bulgaria, Macedonia\n|-\n| data-sort-value=\"Black\"| ''[[The Black Hen]]'' || ''Kalo Pothi'' || data-sort-value=\"Bham\"| [[Min Bahadur Bham]] || Nepal, France, Germany\n|-\n| colspan=2| ''[[Light Years (2015 film)|Light Years]]'' || data-sort-value=\"Campbell\"| Esther May Campbell || United Kingdom\n|-\n| ''Mountain'' || ''Montanha'' || data-sort-value=\"Salaviza\"| [[Jo\u00e3o Salaviza]] || Portugal, France\n|-\n| ''[[Motherland (2015 film)|Motherland]]'' || ''Ana Yurdu'' || data-sort-value=\"Tuzen\"| [[Senem T\u00fczen]] || Turkey, Greece\n|-\n| colspan=2 data-sort-value=\"Return\"| ''The Return'' || data-sort-value=\"Zeng\"| Green Zeng || Singapore\n|-\n| colspan=2| ''[[Tanna (film)|Tanna]]'' || data-sort-value=\"Butler\"| [[Martin Butler (director)|Martin Butler]] || Australia\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:95%; margin-top:2px; margin-bottom:0px\"