 Tales\n|-\n! English title\n! Original title\n! Director(s)\n! Production country\n|-\n| {{N/A}} || ''Les 3 Boutons'' || [[Agn\u00e8s Varda]] || France, Italy\n|-\n| {{N/A}} || ''De Djess'' || [[Alice Rohrwacher]] || Italy\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:95%; margin-top:2px; margin-bottom:0px\"\n! colspan=4| Special projects\n|-\n! English title\n! Original title\n! Director(s)\n! Production country\n|-\n| colspan=2| ''Bangland'' || Lorenzo Berghella || Italy\n|-\n| ''The Country Where Trees Fly. Eugenio Barba and the Days of Odin'' || ''Il paese dove gli alberi volano. Eugenio Barba e i giorni dell'Odin'' || Davide Barletti, Jacopo Quadri || Italy\n|-\n| ''Dreams of the Salt Lake'' || ''I sogni del lago salato'' || [[Andrea Segre]] || Italy\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:95%; margin-top:2px\"\n! colspan=4| Lux Prize\n|-\n! English title\n! Original title\n! Director(s)\n! Production country\n|-\n| colspan=2| ''[[Mediterranea (film)|Mediterranea]]'' || [[Jonas Carpignano]] || Italy, United States, Germany, France, Qatar\n|-\n| colspan=2| ''[[Mustang (film)|Mustang]]'' || [[Deniz Gamze Erg\u00fcven]] || France, Germany, Turkey, Qatar\n|-\n| ''[[The Lesson (2014 Bulgarian film)|The Lesson]]'' || ''Urok'' || Kristina Grozeva, Petar Valchanov || Bulgaria, Greece\n|}\n:<span style=\"background:#FFDEAD\">Highlighted title</span> indicates the official Venice Days Award winner.\n\n== Awards ==\n[[File:Golden Lion for Best Film frim afar (25530461470).jpg|thumb|[[Lorenzo Vigas]] with the [[Golden Lion]] for ''[[From Afar (film)|From Afar]]'']]\n[[File:Valeria Golino, Venice 2015 (cropped).jpg|thumb|[[Valeria Golino]], winner of the [[Coppa Volpi]]]]\n[[File:Abraham Attah (cropped).jpg|thumb|[[Abraham Attah]], winner of the [[Marcello Mastroianni Award]]]]\n\n===Official selection===\nThe following Official Awards were presented at the 72nd edition:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/72nd-festival/awards/ |title=Official Awards of the 72nd Venice Film Festival |work=labiennale.org |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150926125200/http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/72nd-festival/awards/ |archivedate=26 September 2015 }}</ref><ref name=\"winners\">{{cite web|title=LIVE: The winners of the 72nd Venice Film Festival|url=http://cineuropa.org/nw.aspx?t=newsdetail&did=298479|accessdate=12 September 2015}}</ref>\n\n'''In Competition (Venezia 72)'''\n*[[Golden Lion]]: ''[[From Afar (film)|From Afar]]'' by [[Lorenzo Vigas]]\n*[[Silver Lion|Silver Lion for Best Director]]: [[Pablo Trapero]] for ''[[The Clan (2015 film)|The Clan]]''\n*[[Grand Jury Prize (Venice Film Festival)|Grand Jury Prize]]: ''[[Anomalisa]]'' by [[Charlie Kaufman]] and [[Duke Johnson (director)|Duke Johnson]]\n*[[Volpi Cup for Best Actor]]: [[Fabrice Luchini]] for ''[[Courted (film)|Courted]]''\n*[[Volpi Cup for Best Actress]]: [[Valeria Golino]] for ''[[Per amor vostro]]''\n*[[Marcello Mastroianni Award]]: [[Abraham Attah]] for ''[[Beasts of No Nation (film)|Beasts of No Nation]]''\n*Best Screenplay Award: [[Christian Vincent (director)|Christian Vincent]] for ''[[Courted (film)|Courted]]''\n*[[Special Jury Prize (Venice Film Festival)|Special Jury Prize]]: ''[[Frenzy (2015 film)|Frenzy]]'' by [[Emin Alper]]\n\n'''Horizons (Orizzonti)'''\n*Best Film: ''[[Free in Deed]]'' by [[Jake Mahaffy]]\n*Best Director: [[Brady Corbet]] for ''[[The Childhood of a Leader (film)|The Childhood of a Leader]]''\n*Special Jury Prize: ''[[Neon Bull]]'' by [[Gabriel Mascaro]]\n*Special Prize For Best Actor or Actress: Dominique Leborne for ''[[Temp\u00eate (film)|Temp\u00eate]]''\n*Horizons Prize for Best Short: ''[[Belladonna (short film)|Belladonna]]'' by Dubravka Turic\n\n'''Lion of the Future''' \n:Luigi De Laurentiis Award for a Debut Film: ''The Childhood of a Leader'' by Brady Corbet (Horizons)<ref>{{cite web|title=Venice: Robert Pattinson-Starrer 'Childhood of a Leader' Wins Best Debut Film|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/venice-robert-pattinson-starrer-childhood-822550|accessdate=12 September 2015}}</ref>\n\n'''Venice Classics Awards'''\n*Best Documentary on Cinema: ''The 1000 Eyes of Dr. Maddin'' by Yves Montmayeur\n*Best Restored Film: ''[[Sal\u00f2, or the 120 Days of Sodom]]'' by [[Pier Paolo Pasolini]]\n\n'''Special Awards'''\n*[[Golden Lion#Golden Lion Honorary Award|Golden Lion For Lifetime Achievement]]: [[Bertrand Tavernier]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ilgazzettino.it/CULTURA/cinema_francese_tavernier_leone_d_amp_39_oro_carriera/notizie/1555371.shtml|title=Tavernier, Leone alla carriera: \"Fiero di ci\u00f2 che ho fatto\"|work=ilgazzettino.it}}</ref>\n*Jaeger-LeCoultre Glory to the Filmmaker Award: [[Brian De Palma]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dazebaonews.it/cultura/item/36049-venezia-72-il-premio-jaeger-lecoultre-glory-to-the-filmaker-a-brian-de-palma.html|title=Venezia 72. Il premio Jaeger-LeCoultre Glory to the Filmaker a Brian De Palma|author=Redazione|work=dazebaonews.it}}</ref>\n*Persol Tribute To Visionary Talent Award: [[Jonathan Demme]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.luukmagazine.com/jonathan-demme-vince-il-persol-tribute-to-visionary-talent-award-2015/|title=Jonathan Demme vince il Persol Tribute to Visionary Talent Award 2015|work=luukmagazine.com|date=8 September 2015|accessdate=9 September 2015}}</ref>\n*L'Or\u00e9al Paris per il Cinema Award: Valentina Corti\n\n===Autonomous sections===\nThe following official and collateral awards were conferred to films of the autonomous sections:<ref name=\"collateral\">{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/event/ev0000681/2015/1/ |title=Venice Film Festival 2015 Awards |work=imdb.com |accessdate=7 May 2018}}</ref>\n\n'''30th Venice International Critics' Week'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sicvenezia.it/3559/edizione-2015/news-2015/premio-del-pubblico-pietro-barzisa-a-tanna/?lang=en |title=All Awards 2015 announced: Audience Award Pietro Barzisa to Tanna by Bentley Dean and Martin Butler}}</ref> \n*Audience Award Pietro Barzisa: ''[[Tanna (film)|Tanna]]'' by [[Bentley Dean]] and [[Martin Butler (director)|Martin Butler]]\n* Fedeora Awards (Critics' Week):\n**Best Film: ''[[The Black Hen]]'' by [[Min Bahadur Bham]]\n**Best Cinematography: [[Bentley Dean]] for ''[[Tanna (film)|Tanna]]''\n\n'''Venice Days'''<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.venice-days.com/NEWS.asp?id=1&id_dettaglio=652&lang=eng |title=Palmares 2015 |work=Venice Days}}</ref>\n*Venice Days Award: ''[[Early Winter (film)|Early Winter]]'' by [[Michael Rowe (director)|Michael Rowe]]\n*BNL People's Choice Award: ''[[As I Open My Eyes]]'' by  [[Leyla Bouzid]]\n*Europa Cinemas Label Award for Best European Film: ''[[As I Open My Eyes]]'' by  [[Leyla Bouzid]] \n*Laguna Sud Award:\n**Best Film: ''[[Lolo (film)|Lolo]]'' directed by [[Julie Delpy]]\n**Best Italian Discovery: ''[[Arianna (film 2015)|Arianna]]'' directed by [[Carlo Lavagna]]\n* Francesco Pasinetti (SNGCI) Award - Special mentions:\n**''[[First Light (film)|First Light]]'' (''La prima luce'') by [[Vincenzo Marra]]\n**[[Vincenzo Marra]] (director) and [[Riccardo Scamarcio]] (leading actor) for 'First Light'''\n* Fedeora Awards (Venice Days):\n**Best Film: ''[[Underground Fragrance]]'' directed by [[Pengfei]] \n**Best Director of a Debut Film: Ruchika Oberoi for ''[[Island City (2015 film)|Island City]]''\n**Best Actress in a Debut Film: Ondina Quadri for ''Arianna''\n\n===Other collateral awards===\nThe following collateral awards were conferred to films of the official selection:<ref name=\"collateral\" />\n* [[FIPRESCI|FIPRESCI Awards]]<ref name=\"fipresci\">{{cite web|url=http://www.fipresci.org/festival-reports/2015/venice |title=FIPRESCI - Venice Awards 2015 |work=fipresci.org |accessdate=5 May 2018}}</ref>\n**Best Film (Main competition): ''[[Blood of My Blood (2015 film)|Blood of My Blood]]'' (''Sangue del mio sangue'') by [[Marco Bellocchio]]\n**Best Film (Horizons): ''[[Wednesday, 9 May]]'' (''Chaharshanbeh, 19 Ordibehesht'') by [[Vahid Jalilvand]]\n::Special mention: ''[[The Childhood of a Leader (film)|The Childhood of a Leader]]'' by [[Brady Corbet]]\n* [[SIGNIS|SIGNIS Award]]: ''[[Behemoth (2015 film)|Behemoth]]'' (''Bei xi mo shou'') by [[Zhao Liang (director)|Zhao Liang]]\n::Special mention: ''[[The Wait (2015 film)|The Wait]]'' (''L'attesa'') by [[Piero Messina]]\n* Francesco Pasinetti (SNGCI) Award:\n**Best Film: ''[[Don't Be Bad]]'' (''Non essere cattivo'') by  [[Claudio Caligari]]\n**Best Actor: [[Luca Marinelli]] for ''Don't Be Bad'' (Out of competition) \n**Best Actress: [[Valeria Golino]] for ''[[Per amor vostro|For Your Love]]''\n* Leoncino d'Oro Agiscuola Award: ''The Wait'' (''L'attesa'') by Piero Messina\n* Brian Award: ''[[Spotlight (film)|Spotlight]]'' by [[Tom McCarthy (director)|Tom McCarthy]]\n* [[Queer Lion]]: ''[[The Danish Girl (film)|The Danish Girl]]'' by [[Tom Hooper]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Eddie Redmayne\u2019s \u2018The Danish Girl\u2019 Wins Venice\u2019s Queer Lion Award as Oscar Buzz Mounts|url=https://www.thewrap.com/eddie-redmaynes-the-danish-girl-wins-venices-queer-lion-award-as-oscar-buzz-mounts/|accessdate=12 September 2015}}</ref>\n::Special mention: ''Baby Bump'' by Kuba Czekaj\n* Arca CinemaGiovani Award:\n**Best Film of Venezia 72: ''[[Frenzy (2015 film)|Frenzy]]'' by [[Emin Alper]]\n**Best Italian Film: ''[[Burning Love (film)|Burning Love]]'' (''Pecore in erba'') by Alberto Caviglia (Horizons)\n*FEDIC Award: ''Don't Be Bad'' directed by Claudio Caligari (Out of competition)\n::Special mention: ''[[The Wait (2015 film)|The Wait]]'' directed by [[Piero Messina]]\n* Fedeora Awards - Best Euro-Mediterranean film: ''[[Francofonia]]'' directed by [[Alexander Sokurov]]\n* Fondazione Mimmo Rotella Award: [[Alexander Sokurov]] for ''[[Francofonia]]''\n::Special Award: [[Johnny Depp]] and [[Terry Gilliam]]\n* 2nd Starlight Cinema Awards'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.comingsoon.it/news/?source=cinema&key=50196|title=Starlight Cinema Award 2015: i premiati a Venezia|work=ComingSoon.it}}</ref>\n**Career Award: [[Lina Wertmuller]]\n**International Award: [[Paz Vega]]\n**Best Film: [[Matteo Garrone|Matteo Garrone's]] ''[[Tale of Tales (2015 film)|Tale of Tales]]''\n**Best breakthrough actress of the year: Silvia D\u2019Amico\n***Best breakthrough actor of the year: Giovanni Anzaldo\n**Humanitarian Award: Myriam Catania\n**Special Mention: Lucana Film Commission\n**Best breakthrough production: ''Buena Onda'' by [[Riccardo Scamarcio]]\n**Intercultural Award: [[Reynaldo Gianecchini]]\n* Green Drop Award: ''[[Behemoth (2015 film)|Behemoth]]'' directed by [[Zhao Liang (director)|Zhao Liang]]\n* Vittorio Veneto Film Festival Young Jury award: ''[[Remember (2015 film)|Remember]]'' directed by [[Atom Egoyan]]\n::Special mention: ''[[11 Minutes (film)|11 Minutes]]'' directed by [[Jerzy Skolimowski]]\n* Gold Mouse: ''[[Rabin, the Last Day]]'' directed by [[Amos Gitai]]\n* Silver Mouse: ''[[Spotlight (film)|Spotlight]]'' directed by [[Tom McCarthy (director)|Tom McCarthy]]\n* Future Film Festival Digital Award: ''[[Anomalisa]]'' by [[Charlie Kaufman]] and [[Duke Johnson (director)|Duke Johnson]]\n::Special mention: ''[[Heart of a Dog]]'' by [[Laurie Anderson]]\n* P. Nazareno Taddei Award: ''[[Marguerite (2015 film)|Marguerite]]'' by [[Xavier Giannoli]]\n* Lanterna Magica (CGS) Award: ''Blanka'' by Kohki Hasei\n* Open Award: Carlotta Cerquetti for ''Harry\u2019s Bar''\n* Lina Mangiacapre Award: [[Laurie Anderson]] for ''[[Heart of a Dog (2015 film)|Heart of a Dog]]''\n* Gillo Pontecorvo - Arcobaleno Latino Award: ''[[Don't Be Bad]]'' by [[Claudio Caligari]]\n* INTERFILM Award: ''[[Wednesday, 9 May]]'' by [[Vahid Jalilvand]]\n* \"Civitas Vitae prossima\" Award: [[Alberto Caviglia]] for ''[[Pecore in erba]]''\n* Soundtrack Stars Award:\n**''[[A Bigger Splash (2015 film)|A Bigger Splash]]'' by [[Luca Guadagnino]]\n**''[[Equals (film)|Equals]]'' by [[Drake Doremus]]\n**Award for Lifetime Achievement: [[Nicola Piovani]]\n* Schermi di Qualit\u00e0 \u2013 